module.purpose:
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of a wiring harness assembly design, consisting of


connectors consisting of housing, backshell, contacts, inserts, seals, plugs and other auxiliary components;

single electrical or optical wires and cables with multiple wires, including shields;

identification of terminal features at the end of wires and intermediate positions;

identification of terminal features on various kinds of contacts, 
		       including connector contacts, lugs, terminals, splices and others;

identification of intended connection purpose of a terminal feature, including crimp, solder, welding, push, screw, clamp an others;

detailed join information of a pair of terminal features and how the joint is realized by crimping, soldering, and others;

topological segment structure, consisting of connected vertices and edges with length, and paths through them;

cross sectional segment structure supporting coverings and protections, lacing and twisting 
		    of groups and sub-groups of wires, cables and bundles.

     The information kept in a wiring harness assembly design can be associated to 


2D geometry to produce the layout for a formboard in 1:1 scale;

technical drawings for a stick-line representation that is not to scale;

3D geometry by associating edges to curves and vertices to positions.

inscope.li:
wire-list for an wiring harness assembly, consisting of:


wires and cables;

terminal lug;

terminal block;

electrically non conductive through termination;

wire cap;

single and multi pin connector contact;

splice definitions within the harness assembly;

electrical shielding definition in the assembly.

component-list for an wiring harness assembly, consisting of:


connector and associated material;

terminal lug;

terminal block;

electrically non conductive through termination;

wire cap;

single and multi pin connector contact;

splice definitions within the harness assembly;

electrical shielding definition in the assembly;

tape marking.

protection of harness segments including:


grommet;

retention clamps;

sleeving;

overall shielding for one or more harness segments.
